Buteo swainsoni is a medium-sized bird of prey, commonly known as Swainson's Hawk. 
It has a wingspan of 120-137 cm and a length of 48-60 cm. 
The adults have a light-brown upper body and a rufous-colored tail. 
They have a white chin and throat with a distinct dark brown patch on the side of their head. 
The underparts are cream-colored with thin brown streaks. 
Their eyes are dark brown and their beak is black and hooked. 
Swainson's Hawks are found in grasslands, desert, and prairies throughout North and South America.
